Subject: [PATCH] fix: comprehensive runtime fixes for 8 bugs (Audit v11.0)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

8 bug fixes from comprehensive audit v11.0:

BUG-R1 (CRITICAL): Add useGamepad() call in App.tsx for web-based
gamepad detection fallback. Previously gamepad was only detected via
native events — if Shizuku service died, gamepad was invisible.

BUG-R3 (HIGH): Fix permission request code inconsistency.
TouchInjectionPlugin used requestCode 1234, ShizukuPlugin used 100.
Unified to 1234 in both plugins.

BUG-R5 (CRITICAL): Remove overlay detection from App.tsx.
main.tsx already handles overlay rendering via OverlayApp.tsx.
Duplicate detection in App.tsx caused conflict and potential crash.
Removed isNativeOverlayWindow check and inline overlay rendering.

BUG-R6 (HIGH): Add onCommand JavascriptInterface to FloatingOverlayService.
App.tsx called AndroidOverlay.onCommand() but method didn't exist in
WebAppInterface class. Added @JavascriptInterface method.

BUG-R7 (MEDIUM): Fix haptics listener memory leak in useGamepadLoop.
TouchInjection.addListener('onGamepadFeedback') return value was not
saved, so listener was never removed on cleanup. Now saves handle
and removes it in cleanup function.

BUG-R8 (CRITICAL): Fix multi-gamepad — handleButtonBatched always
used gamepadIndex=0. Changed all 2-arg calls to 3-arg calls with
correct gpIdx parameter in GamepadListenerService.kt.

BUG-R9 (HIGH): Fix config not sent to overlay WebView.
Replaced window.dispatchEvent(MessageEvent) with window.injectConfig()
in FloatingOverlayService.java (3 locations). MessageEvent origin
check fails in Capacitor WebView — injectConfig is the correct API.

BUG-R10 (LOW): Fix version-check.yml typo 'branches: ain]' -> 'branches: [main]'.
Used multi-line YAML syntax to avoid [main] being interpreted as
ANSI escape sequence.
